observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the:

a. Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical inventory and submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment not later than January 31 of each year; and (ii) ensure the proper tagging of all properties and adopt a standardized system of property numbering;

b. Acting GSO to (i) maintain Property Cards based on source documents, such as Purchase Orders, Delivery Receipts/Invoices, and Inspection and Acceptance Reports, ensuring that all required details are accurately and completely recorded for each type of property; (ii) utilize Annex C – List of Non-Existing/Missing Property, Plant, and Equipment (PPE), as prescribed under COA Circular No. 2020-006; and (iii) maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map and Local Road Network Property Card;

c. Municipal Accountant to complete all required details of the Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Card (PPELC);

d. Municipal Engineering Office to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Acting GSO the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects as basis of the Municipal Accountant to record the same in the books of accounts; and

e. Municipal Assessor to immediately survey the landholdings declared under the name of the Municipality and assist the Acting General Services Officer to undertake the necessary actions for the registration and titling of the landholdings.

We reiterated our recommendations with modifications and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the:

Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical inventory and submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment not later than January 31 of each year;

Acting GSO to (i) maintain Property Cards for each type of property in coordination with the Office of the Municipal Accountant; (ii) issue the corresponding Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) to fix the accountability of the end-user over the property; and (iii) maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map and Local Road Network Property Card;

Representative of the office receiving any property from any source to secure all turnover documents or deed of donation from the donor and furnish the Accounting and GSO Office a copy for proper recognition of the same in the books of accounts simultaneous with the fixing of accountability therefor;

Municipal Accountant to (i) prepare and maintain Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Card (PPELC), Construction-in-Progress Ledger Cards (CIPLC) and Real Property Ledger Cards (RPLC); (ii) recognize donated properties in the books of accounts; and (iii) draw the necessary journal entry voucher/s to reflect the adjustments on depreciation and misclassified PPEs;

Municipal Engineering Office to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Acting GSO the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects and, on the basis of which, the Municipal Accountant to record the same in the books of accounts; and

Municipal Assessor to immediately survey the landholdings declared under the name of the Municipality and assist the Municipal Treasurer (or General Services Officer) in undertaking the necessary actions for the registration and titling of the landholdings.

We commended the Municipality for adhering to the rules on the appropriation and utilization of the 20% Development Fund for projects that are necessary and essential to the promotion of the general welfare of its constituents and ensuring that PPAs do not fall within the purview of ineligible expenditures enumerated in Section 3.2.5 of DBM-DOF-DILG JMC No. 1 dated November 4, 2020. 

However, we recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to direct the:

Local Development Council to (i) specify the projects, programs and activities under the Development fund; (ii) stop the practice of lump sum budgeting and inclusion of generic items in the Annual Investment Plan and Annual Budget, otherwise secure prior authority from the Local Sanggunian; and (iii) ensure that the development projects to be funded out of the 20% DF are well planned and procurement and implementation ready;

Chairman and Members of the BAC and TWG to (i) carefully scrutinize the documentary requirements submitted by the bidder and conduct verification thereof to ascertain any commitment by the latter and prevent any conflicting information thereon; and (ii) ensure the submission by the winning bidder of a valid performance security prior to signing of the contract to safeguard the government from any untoward act of the former, if there be any; 

Municipal Engineer to (i) conduct close monitoring during project implementation and ensure compliance by the contractor with the requirements of the contract; and (ii) prepare variation order should a change of work from the original plan occur; and

Municipal Accountant, in close coordination with the BAC, to (i) subject progress payments to the retention fee of ten percent (10%) until fifty percent (50%) completion of the value of works provided it is satisfactorily done and on schedule; (ii) submit all the necessary supporting documents for the identified contracts; and (iii) verify all supporting documents as to completeness and see to it that the same are attached to the disbursement vouchers before effecting payments thereof.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the:
Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical inventory and submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment not later than January 31 of each year;
Acting GSO to (i) maintain Property Cards for each type of property in coordination with the Office of the Municipal Accountant; (ii) issue the corresponding Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) to fix the accountability of the end-user over the property; and (iii) maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map and Local Road Network Property Card;
Representative of any office receiving any property from any source secure all turnover documents or deed of donation from the donor and furnish the Accounting and GSO Office a copy for proper recognition of the same in the books of accounts simultaneous with the fixing of accountability therefor;
