Management Comment: The representative of the Rural Health Unit (RHU) in charge in filing of records furnished the Office of the Municipal Accountant turn-over documents, such as Deed of Donation for the One (1) unit Ambulance with accessories donated by the Department of Health (DOH).
The Municipal Accountant have (i) complied and recognized the said donated property in the book of accounts under JEV No. 100-22-03-446 dated 3/7/2022 and (ii) prepared and updated the Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELC) with Lapsing Schedules.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to:
instruct the Municipal Planning and Development Officer and Municipal Engineer to (i) ensure that all identified projects will be implemented without further delay; and (ii) continue to monitor and supervise the implementation of projects under the development fund;
direct the Local Development Council to (i) specify the projects, programs and activities under the Development fund; and (ii) stop the practice of lump sum budgeting and inclusion of generic items in the Annual Investment Plan and Annual Budget, otherwise secure prior authority from the Local Sanggunian;
ensure that all changes in the Annual Investment Program shall be reviewed and endorsed by the Local Development Council;
fast track the accomplishment of Deeds of Donation and all other transfer and receipt documents for the donated ambulances to ensure proper recognition for both books of the donor and donee; and
instruct the Municipal Accountant to (i) review the recognition of transactions for the land and land improvements and draw correcting entries therefor; and (ii) reconcile her records with the Municipal Engineer and re-evaluate the nature and intent of expenditures in order to properly recognize all improvements made on various properties in the books of accounts and adjust the cost of PPE when applicable.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the Accounting Office, Treasury Office and the Inventory Committee, as the case may be, to 

(a) conduct complete physical inventory taking  and submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment not later than January 31 of each year; 

(b) prepare and maintain property cards  for each category of assets starting with current year’s acquisition; 

(c) adopt all the principles prescribed in PPSAS 17 for proper accounting of PPEs and fair presentation of the asset accounts in the financial statements 

(d) facilitate confirmation with the Land Registration Authority (LRA) and seek technical assistance, if necessary, to be able to have the remaining 20 lots titled in the name of the Municipality of Apalit.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
lead the Local Development Council in improving the planning and project identification of projects for funding under the 20% Development Fund by referring to the latest guidelines under DILG-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2017 – 1 dated February 22, 2017, giving priority to capital investments;
continue to invest in high-impact capital expenditure projects in the utilization of its 20% Development Fund and refrain from proposing non-capital investment projects/programs under the Fund.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the 

(a) Municipal Accountant and the designated Property Officer to continue accelerating joint efforts towards the reconciliation of the balances per books (All Funds) with that of the inventory report; 

(b) Municipal Treasury, Supply Officer and the Municipal Assessor to ascertain the status of parcels of land owned by the agency with titling issues and work for the titling thereof in the name of the Municipality of Apalit, assuming funds have been provided therefor.

